articularly for mexico drawn from these successful programs in brazil colombia and the us the povgov program anticipates that this series will be useful as mexico and other latin american countries explore new approaches to solve their development challenges related links beatriz magaloni associate professor of political science and cddrl affiliated faculty changing relationships between police and society what inspiring experiences in rio de janeiro medellin and the united states can teach mexico stephanie gimenez stahlberg beatriz magaloni cddrl program on poverty and governance policy brief no 1 2011 pdf+ rebuilding the social fabric in places of violence project search news of interest researchers explore potential solutions to mexican crime and violence november 22 2011 cisac fsi stanford cddrl announcement mexico conference to draw international experts august 24 2011 cddrl fsi stanford news chiapas research examines women and governance august 23 2011 news about the program on poverty and governance august 1 2011 announcement support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 725 9739 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
